  "modName": "Respectful Lydia - Willing Burden Carrier",
  "summary": "Replace Lydia\\'s \\\"I am swoooorn to carry your burden\\\" remark with something more appropriate and less annoying.",
  "descriptionHtml": "Update: You can now download a separate ESP that will change the corresponding subtitle, for those who use subtitles. These were created by nathanlonghair and have not been tested by me. I\\'d love to pack everything into an ESP but I just don\\'t have the time to figure it out right now.\r\n\r\nThis mod replaces Lydia\\'s sarcastic, disrepectful \\\"I am swoooorn to carry your burden\\\" with another saying of your choice. I never could figure out why she sounds completely subservient in every way, but when you want to give her some nice armor, she makes a snide remark.\r\n\r\nTo install, choose which saying you would like her to say, then copy the corresponding data folder into your Skyrim folder.\r\n\r\nChoose from the three following options:\r\n\r\n\\\"As you wish, my Thane.\\\"\r\n\\\"Let\\'s see it.\\\"\r\n\\\"What do you want me to carry?\\\"\r\n\r\nNote that these are all part of her original voice package.\r\n\r\nIf you would like her to be silent when giving her items, you can use the \\\"no-burden\\\" mod [url=http://www.skyrimnexus.com/downloads/file.php?id=1183]located here[/url] (not my mod). Special thanks to the creator of that mod for sharing the file name.",
